    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNeovim just adds default keymaps `an` and `in` in visual mode to do incremental/decremental selection with LSP, which is great.\n\nHowever, I cannot seem to make them work in operator-pending mode to use the \"node range\" as a text object:\n\n```lua\nvim.keymap.set('o', 'an', '<Cmd>sil! norm van<CR>', { noremap = false, desc = 'Around range' })\n```\n\nThe above works with nvim-treesitter (master branch) with\n\n```lua\nincremental_selection = {\n  enable = true,\n  keymaps = {\n    init_selection = false,\n    node_incremental = 'an',\n    node_decremental = 'in',\n  },\n},\n```\n\nWith visual-mode `an` defined as treesitter incremental selection and the operator-pending-mode `an` as above, I can do `dan` or `can` to delete or change around current range. But with the new LSP default `an`, `dap`/`can` just select the range without deleting.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`dan`/`can` should work as expected.",
